By MATTHEW GOLDSTEIN
A panel plans to hold a hearing next week on ways to “protect the financial sector” from cyberattacks, but for now there are no plans to have anyone from the financial services industry testify.
December 5, 2014, Friday


Home Depot Posts a Strong 3rd Quarter Despite a Data Breach Disclosure
By HIROKO TABUCHI
The home improvement retailer, the target of a cyberattack affecting as many as 56 million customers, beat analysts’ expectations with $1.5 billion in net earnings.
November 19, 2014, Wednesday




Home Depot Says Hackers Also Stole Email Addresses
By NICOLE PERLROTH
Hackers took 53 million email addresses in addition to the payment card details of 56 million of its customers during this year’s data breach, the retailer disclosed.
November 6, 2014, Thursday





